Patch Set 2:

Oh, duh, make check was discussed above.

Also, if anything like effort seems to be resulting from this repo, I'm happy to take it off the list and I can get it removed from the release process before the next release.

I'll try a build without 'make check' now.

Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

Yah, let's ignore 'make check' issues. If I fix that one file's trailing whitespace, then we get a whole slew of other make check issues. Not worth it.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1 Integration-Approval+1

After eliding 'make check', a full clean build worked for me. Oh the pain you needed to do for a non-dirty work tree for 'bits-upload'!  Installed on nightly-2 and services are running. CA agents (at least cainstsvc) are broken on latest platforms and we're sunsetting it, so I haven't dived into deeper testing.
